The paper deals with learning text representations directly from raw character sequences, which is a common task in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of a Simple recurrent Network to predict the next character in text suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE). Finally, the task of recognizing spans of text containing programming language code suggests a focus on information retrieval (cs.IR).
